# LoadZone Data Fetching

- Read initial page data in server components with Prisma or server-side helpers.
- Do not use client-side fetching for first render if the data can be loaded on the server.
- Use Server Actions for one-shot form submissions and CRUD mutations.
- Revalidate affected paths or tags after writes.
- Reserve client-side fetching libraries for genuinely interactive cases only:
  polling, optimistic updates, live refresh, or complex client state sync.
- Avoid adding extra API layers for internal page data unless there is a real integration boundary.
